HEADWORD: Haybote
<hw>Hay"bote`</hw> <pr>(h⟦amac⟧"b⟦omac⟧t`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Hay</er> hedge, and <er>Bote</er>, and cf.
<er>Hedgebote</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Eng. Law.)</fld> <def>An allowance of
wood to a tenant for repairing his hedges or fences; hedgebote. See
<er>Bote</er>.</def> <rj><au>Blackstone.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

